    "type": "SensitivityAnalysis",
    "name": "Global sensitivity analysis — material properties and contact parameters",
    "description": "Sobol first-order and total-order sensitivity indices computed for the three QoIs (stiffness, yield force, force at 40 mm) with respect to seven input parameters: Ti-6Al-4V elastic modulus, yield strength, tangent modulus, UHMWPE block modulus, screw-rod contact friction coefficient, screw insertion angle, and rod diameter. Elastic modulus and yield strength account for 61% and 24% of stiffness QoI variance respectively; friction coefficient contributes <3% to all QoIs confirming insensitivity to contact parameter uncertainty. Results justify the parameter uncertainty bounds used in the Monte Carlo UQ propagation."
